description:
Biography

Jutta Leerdam is a Dutch speed skater born on December 30, 1998. She quickly made a name for herself in the world of speed skating, winning numerous national and international titles. Leerdam's breakthrough came in 2020 when she claimed the World Sprint Speed Skating Championships. Known for her powerful strides and graceful technique, she continues to inspire young athletes and remains a prominent figure in the sport.
